===Etymology===
From the [[w:Slavic languages|Slavic]] suffix ({{etyl|ru}}: {{term|lang=ru|-ник|tr=-nik}}). This suffix experienced a surge in English coinages for nicknames and diminutives after the 1957 Soviet launch of the first [[w:Sputnik program|Sputnik satellite]].  English usage is heavily influenced by {{etyl|yi}} usage of {{term||-nik}} and similar borrowed words ([[nogoodnik]], [[nudnik]], [[kibbutznik]]).

===Suffix===
'''-nik'''

# Appended to words to create a [[nickname]] for a person who [[exemplify|exemplifies]], [[endorse]]s, or is associated with the thing or quality specified (by the base form), often a particular [[ideology]] or preference.

