===Etymology===
From {{proto|Slavic|-(ь)nikъ|lang=sh}}, itself originally by [[nominalization]] of adjectives in *{{term||-ьnъ}} with the suffix *{{term||-ikъ|}} (whence {{term|-ik|lang=sh}}). The suffix originates from {{proto|Balto-Slavic|lang=sh}} period; compare with dialectal Lithuanian {{term|laukinykas|lauk-inykas|peasant, farmer|lang=lt}} (from {{term|laukas|laũkas|field|lang=lt}}) and Old Prussian {{term|laukinikis|lauk-inikis|vassal|lang=prg}}.

